('<li>Place no weight on your injured leg or arm.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>While you stand or walk, you must hold your injured leg off the floor.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Do not touch the floor with your injured leg.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>', '<li>When you stand or walk, you may only touch the floor for balance.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Do not place any body weight on your leg. Imagine you have an egg under your foot that you are not to crush.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>', '<li>When you stand or walk, you may place some of your body weight on your injured leg.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The weight may be gradually increased up to 50% of the body weight. Check the end of this booklet for any specific instructions by your clinician.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>', '<li>When you stand or walk, place only as much weight as feels comfortable on your injured leg or arm.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Let pain be your guide. If you feel pain, place less weight on the leg or arm.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>', '<li>You may place your full body weight on your leg or arm.\r\n<br>\r\n</li>');

