('				<div class="col-md-12">\r\n                    <p class="subtitle-content">Going upstairs using crutches</p>\r\n                    <p>Your clinician has told you that you are not allowed to put your foot down at all on your affected leg. This make stair climbing a little difficult so you should consider shuffling up the stairs on your bottom. However, if you feel able to use the one crutch (and handrail) to go upstairs ask somebody to be close behind you to begin with just in case you need help.</p>\r\n					<p>When going up stairs, bend your knee and keep your foot behind you, on the bad side, so it doesn''t clip the steps as you go up.</p>\r\n                    <p>Start close to the bottom step, place one hand on the handrail and hold the crutches in the other hand as shown above. Then:<br></p>\r\n                    <div class="row">\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/good-leg.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>Place your weight equally through the handrail and crutch as you hop up to the next step,</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/injured-leg.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>Straighten your good leg and bring your bad leg and...</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/crutches.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>...crutches to the side of it.</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="col-md-12">\r\n                    <p class="subtitle-content">Going Downstairs using crutches</p>\r\n                    <p>Your clinician has told you that you are not allowed to put your foot down at all on your affected leg. This makes going downstairs a little difficult so you should consider shuffling downstairs on your bottom. However, if you feel able to descend using the one crutch (and handrail) ask somebody to be close to you initially just in case you need help.</p>\r\n					<p>When going downstairs,</p>\r\n                    <div class="row">\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/crutches.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>Put the crutches on the lower step and...<br></p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/injured-leg.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>...extend your bad leg in front of you making sure it won''t clip the step as you go down.</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/good-leg.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>Place your weight through the crutches as you hop down with your good leg.</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>', '				<div class="col-md-12">\r\n                    <p class="subtitle-content">Going upstairs using crutches</p>\r\n                    <p>Your clinician has told you that you are not allowed to put your foot down at all on your affected leg. This make stair climbing a little difficult so you should consider shuffling up the stairs on your bottom. However, if you feel able to use the one crutch (and handrail) to go upstairs ask somebody to be close behind you to begin with just in case you need help.</p>\r\n					<p>When going up stairs, bend your knee and keep your foot behind you, on the bad side, so it doesn''t clip the steps as you go up.</p>\r\n                    <p>Start close to the bottom step, place one hand on the handrail and hold the crutches in the other hand as shown above. Then:<br></p>\r\n                    <div class="row">\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/good-leg.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                            <p>Place your weight equally through the handrail and crutch as you hop up to the next step,</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="text-center col-md-4 vcenter col-sm-4 col-xs-4 col-lg-4"> \r\n                            <img src="img/injured-leg.png" class="img-responsive center-block">\r\n                        </div><!--\r\n                        --><div class="col-md-8 vcenter col-sm-8 col-xs-8 col-lg-8"> \r\n                    